    "description": "The 3e-030-2 Security Server Cryptographic Core (Version 4.0) provides FIPS 140-2 validated cryptographic functionality for the 3eTI Security Server product, a RADIUS based Authentication Server, capable of EAP-TLS authentication of wireless client, support of JITC DoD-signed certificates for PKI usage, and full 802.11i support. The 3e-030-2 provides the following FIPS-approved cryptographic algorithms: AES, SHA-1, SHA-2, HMAC, RSA DSA ECDSA sign/verify, FIPS 186-2 PRNG. The 3e-030-2 also supports the following non-FIPS cryptographic algorithms: Diffie Hellman, ECDH and MD5",
